Art is powerful. Each work has the ability to bring vibrancy, perspective, joy, depth, thoughtfulness and personality into a space. But it can also be prohibitively expensive and inaccessible for many…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
In an effort to bring more art into your home, we’re partnering with @allisontunis for this seasons’ #AccessibleArt project.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Most online orders come with a marketing or informational insert that typically gets tossed straight into the bin upon opening. But we want every part of your Free Label order to be useful and joyful. So instead, we include a beautiful high-quality art print - with important info about garment care, materials, returns, etc - that’s designed to live a long and meaningful life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Whether you frame this piece, stick it up on your fridge, gift it by repurposing it as a card or prop it up on your desk, we hope this little piece of #AccessibleArt finds a home in your space and becomes a daily catalyst for joy and perspective.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A message from the artist: 
“I strive to create joyful images of all different types of people, especially those who have historically been underrepresented. Making that representation accessible outside of art spaces is hugely important, and I’m excited to collaborate with Free Label to bring an unexpected extra bit of colour into your life.” -@allisontunis
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Where will you put your #AccessibleArt print?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#accesibleart #lineart #bodypositiveart #supportlocalartists #artforeverybody

When I first set out to make a bra, I dreamt up my dream bra: soft, comfortable, wire-free, and medium support - Aka the Andie. My b cup was thrilled and ever since it’s been my go to style. But I soon realized that it’s impossible to make a single style work for everybody and every bust. So next came the Becky: a higher coverage bra for bigger busts. And then the Dani: a nursing friendly option for bigger busts too! Each bra is designed with unique features that cater to different needs in the hopes that everyone can find SOMETHING they like enough to say goodbye to underwire forever.

Most recently, we launched the Carrie. FL’s first non reversible, adjustable, spaghetti strap bralette. The Carrie sold out much quicker than anticipated and quickly reached #1 on our most requested waitlist item! Turns out it filled a much needed gap in our bra line up, so we started working very quickly to restock as soon as possible and then thought, why not also restock this year’s #1 bestseller as well… the Dani Bra!

We were able to work with our production partners to do a small and quick restock for the Carrie and Dani before the end of the year (yay)! This means our entire range of bamboo bras will have at least some inventory online at once, so you can pick your perfect fit.

If you haven’t tried it yet, the new Carrie Bra is the perfect option if you’re looking for a lower coverage option and thin adjustable straps that you can easily layer under your tops. If you have a heavier bust and desire more support and compression, the Dani might be the perfect option for you! Need help picking a style? Send us a DM! 

And if you’re already familiar with our bras, which style is your fav? 😏

Restock deets:
Date: Wednesday, December 21
Time: 4:00 pm PST
Styles: The Carrie Bra and The Dani Bra
Colours: Avocado, Clay, Sand, Umber, Storm, and Black

#ditchunderwire #slowfashionmovement #comfort

Big bewbs deserve comfy bras too. Enter, the Dani Bra. 

The Dani has been our #1 best-seller this year with hundreds of 5-star reviews!

What makes the Dani the unicorn of bras? I’m glad you asked...
✨ Deep cross-over for 🍈 separation

I don’t like sales. 
I don’t like them from a consumer OR producer perspective. 
As a consumer, I spent my teens and 20s addicted to markdowns. I’d spend entire weekends at the mall searching for the BEST deals. It felt so good to get that dress that was originally $150 on sale for $75 plus an additional 50% that weekend only! But you know how many times I wore that crazy deal of a dress? Not nearly enough times to make it a “deal”. And having a closet full of stuff I would never pay full price for made me feel horrible. I’d open my closet and feel like I have nothing to wear even though it was full. Because none of it was stuff I would choose for myself. The sale chose it for me.
As a small brand it really bums me out to reduce prices. Just being totally honest here. Most if not ALL major brands include discounts in their pricing structure. They KNOW they will sell X inventory at X discount so they price the garment so it’s still just as profitable.
We don’t do that. I price our garments based on the cost of the labour, fabric, shipping, staffing, overhead, and margin required for sustainable growth. Prices aren’t padded for sales. But sales are a necessary evil of having in-stock product. While we put a lot of time and data into producing what we believe will sell and nothing more, we inevitably end up with some overstock. So once a year we save those pieces to host a sale in an effort to recoup costs.
That said, we’re launching our once a year Archive Sale on December 21st at 4:00pm PST. I do not take this event lightly. But I also know that for many, it can be a chance to invest in FL garments at an accessible price point. Our ultimate goal is for every garment to have a loving home. The Archive Sale helps us do that.
If it serves you, join us for the Archive Sale, where you can save up to 50% off PLUS an additional discount for email subscribers (in lieu of early access). 
And if you’re like 2000’s me and find it difficult to make a thoughtful decision in the face of a sale, join us for a grounding yoga class with @yoga.with.prem on Insta live Dec 19 at 5:00pm PST. Clear your mind, set an intention, and remember - you already have everything you need. 🤍

Things feel… busy right now. Between the bustle of the holidays and impending new year it’s easy to get wrapped up in the chaos during what should be a time of relaxation.

I know how a sale can add to the stress. But I want to remind you that though the Archive Sale can be a great opportunity to shop at a discounted price, its OK if shopping doesn’t align with your goals right now. If you don’t need anything, you can continue to cheer us on from the sidelines without ever adding to cart!

If you DO choose to shop the Archive Sale, we want it to be a feel-good moment that lasts beyond the initial dopamine hit at checkout. I’ve found the key to this is shopping with thoughtful *intention.* Its easier said than done, so we’re bringing in an expert to help you!

Join us on Instagram Live this Monday for a free Restorative Yoga and meditation session led by @yoga.with.prem. This 30-minute session is intended to be a self care tool to help you calm the central nervous system during this noisy season.

We invite every body to join us for this accessible virtual yoga class. It can be practiced anywhere comfortable where you have room to lie down. Whether this is on a yoga mat or your bed, all you need is a pillow or bolster to join in. We hope that by the end of this quick 30 minute session you’ll feel relaxed, clear minded, and ready to go into the holiday season (and/or the Archive Sale) with intention.

Tag a friend who you’d like to practice with ❤️ or share to stories to invite your network!

Whose going to join??

Thank you for this lovely restorative yoga session, @yoga.with.prem ! Such a great way to calm the central nervous system in lead up to the busy holidays.

As we approach the Archive Sale, we want to remind you, while sales can be enticing, you already have everything you need. So please, shop thoughtfully. ❤️

Launch tips. My first tip is… to think deeply about whether you really need something right now. Or whether you are shopping out of boredom, sadness, stress, etc. Shopping is a very temporary and expensive bandaid for deeper issues, so please only purchase what you will love. If you have thought about it and are taking advantage of the Archive Sale discounts, here are a few tips on how to successfully check out with your cart during the madness of a sale. Please note we are on a system that can not save your cart… it’s out of our hands! Please don’t be upset with us!

Ok the tips:
1. Make an account ahead of time and fill out your shipping address and any other helpful info so you can check out quickly
2. Use PayPal - it saves your payment and address information so you can typically check out with one click (pls double check your address is correct)
3. Open each product by right clicking (or if you’re on your phone, hold down on the link) and open to a new page. This way you don’t have to go backward and forward to add to cart, you can right click to open the product and add to cart on separate pages. Your cart will sync.
4. TAKE A MOMENT TO CHECK YOUR SIZES. If you don’t select a size, the browser defaults to XS. You NEED to select your size before adding to cart. There’s limited inventory so if you check out with the wrong stuff, it’s unlikely we’ll be able to change it after for you. And everything is final sale.
5. If you have any questions or problems with your order, rather than DM us, please email customer care Jess at info@freelabel.com ASAP. She’ll be online and is on order duty.
6. Shake it off and have fun! Because of the limited inventory, it’s possible you’ll miss out on something you had your eye on. We do have a great amount of inventory so i’m confident you’ll be able to grab something that works for you, but if you miss out on what you wanted, just remember it’s only clothing! :)

Whew. 2022. That was one for the books. There were many highs, and maybe a similar amount of lows...? It feels like we spent the better part of the year surfing the waves. And you know what? We’re all the more stronger for it.

If I were to choose a word for 2022 it would be resilience.

Despite the challenges, we achieved and conquered so much together. At the end of every year I like to read back my goals from the beginning of the year and see what we did and didn’t do. Here were our goals for 2022:

▫️ cut the cord between myself and social media 🔜 whoops! Not starting off strong with this one. I give myself half marks. It’s tough but I’ve made great strides with the help of Julia 😇

▫️Offer a visual size guide to show our pieces on every size ✔️

▫️fit testing and introduce 5X ✔️

▫️ offer a Reese pant preorder ✔️

▫️continue to improve size demand and production ✔️🔜 this one will also be a work in progress. Forecasting is an art not a science!

▫️ offer one local pop up per season ✔️

▫️ create more video content ✔️

▫️create an activewear capsule 🔜 this one is taking way longer than anticipated!

▫️move into a bigger space that can house our warehouse and office under one roof ✖️ the market said nooooope. We’ll make due until we find the right space!

▫️ find space to be creative again 🔜 still figuring out how to do this… but I have hope!

▫️fine and elegant solution to the ever changing inseam issue ✖️ we did offer two inseams during preorder, but I would love to figure out a solution that doesn’t include keeping double skus of everything!

▫️ send more value add emails 🔜 I give us half marks as we’re just starting to implement this now after deciding to switch email platforms!

Looking back, it feels like a lot. Lots to be proud of! And still lots of room for growth :)

As I take some time to come up with our goals for 2023, I’d love to hear what YOUD like to see from us! Anything we should add to our list for the new year?? Or inspire me and tell me one of your goals for 2023 🤗 

#newyear #2022recap #goalsetting #smallbusinessowner

Are you ready for this?…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
As you may know, we don’t offer swim every year. Over the years I’ve made a couple of small swim collections using dead-stock fabric. But the last time we did swim was in early 2021 when we did a fun swim collaboration with our friends at Nettles Tale - which turned out to be one of our most popular products ever! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If there’s one thing you made clear to us: this community really needs more chic and comfortable swim options!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So after nearly a year and a half of development, we’re juuuust about ready to share what we’ve been dreaming up for you … and it’s one of our most versatile collections… ever.

#postcardsfromjess #swimwear #bathingsuits  #flswim

Is there a more common experience than the feeling of disappointment when trying on a swimsuit that doesn’t fit well? I think in part that’s because swimwear is a category that still lacks diverse representation both throughout the development and marketing processes. It’s so hard to relate to traditional swimwear when all you see are the same bodies in the same bikinis (sorry, a string bikini just isn’t for me!). And so we decided to bring back Free Label swim so we do swimwear YOUR way: comfortable, inclusive, versatile, durable and a little bit sexy ;)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Think:
Bathing suits that make you feel so incredibly and genuinely *you* that those pesky insecurities melt away.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Styles that can be worn in so many different ways that it replaces the need for multiple suits.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Pieces that can be adjusted for low or high coverage depending on how you're feeling and what you're doing that day.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Suits that are both timeless and durable enough so you can wear them endlessly.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
In short. We created a collection of swimwear so YOU could design it for yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
FREE LABEL SWIM PRE-ORDER DETAILS:

𝗪𝗛𝗘𝗡: Thursday, January 12 @ 5:00 pm PST

𝗪𝗛𝗔𝗧: Pre-order for the Saturna Swim Top, Bowen Bottom, and Gabriola One-Piece in Black and Baywatch.

Pre-orders will ship at the beginning of April, just in time for summer :)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
OK, HIT US WITH YOUR QUESTIONS AND/OR EXCITEMENT!!!!

#swimforall #swimwear #flswim #swimsuits #bathingsuit

The Saturna Swim Top started with a conversation about how nice it would be to have a swim top that could be worn a zillion different ways. How much easier packing for a beach getaway would be if you could just pack one top. There is no easy fix for sustainability.

When I set out to make swimwear I knew that it would have an impact on our earth. No amount of recycled this or sustainable that can mask the fact that technical swimwear is made from plastic. It will take centuries to degrade and no amount of green washed marketing will change that.

While I generally choose to avoid synthetics in our garments in favour of compostable textiles, there will always be a need for synthetic fabrics. The most durable performance-oriented fabrics are synthetic. The most sun protectant fabrics are synthetic. We need synthetic stretch to achieve a secure fit for swimwear and activewear. Stretch is a valuable garment feature for bigger, softer bodies. Synthetics are pretty unavoidable in todays world.

But what we CAN do is be really thoughtful about what synthetics we give life to. You can choose to only purchase (and we can choose to only make) synthetic garments that will be worn for years upon years. Every single wear is a decision to be more sustainable.

That’s why we are only offering Free Label Swim as a pre-order. We will only make what will be worn and loved. And we encourage you only to buy what you will wear and love. If you already have a swim suit that brings you joy and is functional - skip the launch! Keep loving your suit. If you’re in need of a new suit? We spent a year and a half designing and sampling the most versatile and beautifully fitting suits possible so we could confidently say “these will be worn a LOT.”

It’s easy to fall into the trap of green marketing but there is NO easy fix for sustainability when it comes to consumption. And recognizing that is a great first step toward more thoughtful decisions.

#slowfashion #myfreelabel #freelabelswim #myfreelabelswim #sustainablefashion

When we set out to design our swim collection, we searched high and low for the *perfect* fabric. We sampled our suits in half a dozen different textiles. Our swim fabric has been custom-milled just for us to meet the FL standards: It's soft, luscious, and silky to the touch but with good compression that hugs you just right and moulds to your body. Durable, totally opaque and colourfast, this bathing suit is made to be worn for decades.

Before we get into the Jacquie Tee, it’s time for another story about how production always keeps us on our toes 😅  
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Last spring, when we did our final run of Supima Cotton tees, we were certain that it was for the very last time. With a huge increase in the cost of this fabric, there wasn’t a way to keep offering these tees at an accessible price point in line with our ethos. Imagine our surprise when one of our factory partners reached out to let us know that they found a few rolls that had been hiding. 🤦🏻‍♀️😂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The good news for you is that this means you have one last chance (we promise this is it this time) to get the perfect basic tee before they’re gone forever.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Jacquie Tee has always been one of our best sellers and it’s actually an offshoot of one of FL’s very first designs! What started as the Betty Tank evolved into a t-shirt version called the Johnny, which lead to the development of the Jaimee Tee, which in turn sparked the Jacquie Tee! (A T-shirt lineage!)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The perfect classic tee is always something I struggled to find. While in theory, it sounds simple as every single store seems to carry one, none of them were quite right. The Jacquie Tee ticks off everything I was looking for. Classic sleeves, a higher crew neck, a gentle curved hem, and a staple body-skimming fit that hangs on your body *just right*. It can be worn on its own or as a base layer. I love it under dresses, overalls, and jumpsuits!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is one of those pieces that you'll want in multiple colours once you try it! I reach for mine weekly and in all four seasons.

Take a walk on the wide side. After an almost 2-year hiatus, the LORETTA PANT is making a comeback… in a brand-new fabric! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
About a year ago, we started receiving daily messages asking if we were going to make the Loretta Pant again and although it wasn’t in our plans… we always give the people what they want!! We took this opportunity to fine-tune the design and make it even better than before.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
First up, new fabric! This 100% Cotton Crepe has beautiful flow, is soft and light to the touch, and is incredibly durable. The *perfect* fabric for a wide-leg pant. I should note that this cotton is different from the last version of Cotton Loretta's and fits more true to size. While a lot of folks chose to size down the last time around, we recommend sticking with your usual FL size for these! This fabric has zero stretch so you want your body measurements to fit within the garment measurements :)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Next, pockets. If you know Free Label, you know how passionate we are about pockets and more specifically, functional pockets. What’s the point if you can’t fit your necessities!? And so we made the pockets a touch deeper 😙👌🏼
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now for the inseam, in our ever-continuing journey to find the ideal inseam length (does this even exist!?), we decided to make the inseam 28” for all sizes. This is a great length for Tags who’s 5’10 AND for Jules at 5’1. Plus the Loretta has a longer-than-average hem, making alterations easier for folks for want an extra inch. Win-win!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We made sure not to change too much though and kept the features like the super high-rise and soft elastic waistband that make the Loretta Pant a fan favourite.

New to wide-leg pants? This is the perfect gateway pant 😉

Every spring I do a closet clean out. I make two piles. One pile of items that no longer fit or I don’t reach for and need to be re-homed. And one pile of super star pieces that I wear over and over again, that I want to keep in mind any time I make a new purchase. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The last time I did my closet clean, I realized that my super star pile had a distinct theme. They were all my comfiest garments that made me feel *me*. I never had to put in effort to style them because they were already the essence of my personal style.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The other pile was made up almost entirely of less comfy structured pieces that felt a bit too tight, pinched at the waist, and took more effort to make an outfit. I’d often reach for those pieces because they were beautiful. But I often put them right back in the closet because I never felt comfortable making an outfit or wearing them all day. They felt like… clothing. But what I realized is that when I get dressed, I’m looking for a second skin.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
That closet clean out really inspired me, so we got straight to work on a very special spring bamboo capsule keeping this lesson in mind. A collection of pieces SO comfy that you don't want to take them off - not even for bed. Fabric and silhouettes that feels like a second skin. Pieces that feel like home.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And of course we had to introduce these new pieces with a 💥bang in a few exciting new colours 😏

Happy Tuesday! I don’t know about you but we’re feeling nice and refreshed after the long weekend here at the office. We’re also feeling a taaad behind. (You know that post long weekend feeling?) That being said, we need just a little more time to prep cut numbers to submit for production so this means that we’re keeping pre-orders open for another 24 HOURS while we get ourselves together. 😅

In the spirit of turning out challenge into an opportunity, we are using this extra time to answer any of your unanswered questions! In particular, we received a handful of similar questions about sizing for Dani Tank this weekend so I thought it would be helpful to share the answer here in case you were wondering the same thing!

It can be difficult to find your perfect fit when different parts of your body fall under different sizes on the size chart and this is actually one of the main struggles that inspired the OG Dani Bra! If you’re in between 3 sizes, I suggest meeting in the middle (for example if your waist is XL and your bust is 3X, choose the 2X) or if you’re in between 2 sizes, think about your preferred fit. You’ll get a more compressive body hugging fit by sizing down and a more relaxed fit by sizing up!

The beauty of our bamboo fabric is that it is S T R E T C H Y so depending on if you like a looser or more compressive fit, you can choose your size accordingly.

And if you’re already familiar with our Dani Bra, we recommend sticking with the same size for the intended fit 🤗

I hope this helps and if you have any other questions, pop them in the comments below 😊️

How annoying is it when you get dressed and you’re juuust about to leave the house when you realize there’s a giant deodorant stain on your top? 🤦🏻‍♀️

I’ll let you in on a secret... you don’t have to change! Try this quick trick for effortless deodorant removal. Simply find another piece of similar fabric or grab the edge of the piece you’re currently wearing and rub it against your deodorant stain. It’s so simple that it seems like a magic trick. For reasons we can’t explain, this helps deodorant marks disappear in a flash. 

P.S. For oil-based deodorant, try this instead. Add a couple of drops of dawn dish soap (I feel like the blue one works best!) along with a dash of warm water to cover your stain and let sit for a few hours or overnight. After it’s had the chance to soak in, give your garment a quick rinse (for smaller stains) or put it through the laundry (for bigger stains). Voila, with this method we’ve been able to remove most stains, especially oil!

Know any other tried and true stain removal hacks? Please share your secrets with us!! 🥰

Wondering which bra style to choose? We're here to support (😉) you! 

We know it can be hard to choose your perfect fit online so we've put together resources to offer the next best thing to an in-person try-on.

1. 'Find Your Best Fit' bra quiz: Answer a quick series of questions and it'll offer you a suggestion for style and size!

2. Visual Size Guide: Folks in every size we carry (5X-XS) modelling a few of our core styles

3. Size Charts: Know your measurements? Find your perfect size!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
P.S. I'll link everything on stories!
 
And a quick breakdown of each style! 

The Dani: Have a larger bust and looking to ditch underwire? Give the Dani Bra a try! This style has specifically been designed to offer support for heavier busts with features such as a deep crossover for bewb separation, 4 layers of fabric for high (yet breathable) compression, and more room for larger cup sizes. Not to mention it's like 2 bras in 1 with its reversible low and high-coverage options! P.S - if you're a nursing mama, this is our most popular style for easy access 😉

The Andie: If you like a thicker strap option but don't need as much support as the Dani, The Andie is a great choice. It has the most shallow cup of all the styles and is great for giving shape and lift to smaller busts. And it's a popular alternative to the Becky Bra. It's also reversible, offering an elegant high neckline or a sultry v-neck. A double whammy!

The Carrie: Looking for a lower coverage option that you can easily layer under your tops? The Carrie sounds like the style for you! It offers bust separating ruching and newly edited not-too-thin straps for additional support. It's best suited for cup sizes AA-G and if you have a heavier bust, you may prefer the Dani.

“Has the bra sizing changed? It feels tighter than before.”
I’ve noticed a couple of folks asking this so I thought I’d share here and the answer is... no, it hasn’t!

Due to the stretchy soft nature of the custom-milled bamboo fabric, it relaxes around half a size with wear and even I still get surprised at how snug a brand-new bra can feel on the first try. I get so used to how perfectly the fabric moulds to my body after constant wear. But keep in mind that there’s a ‘break-in’ period of 3-5 wears and washes until a brand new bra relaxes.

When it comes to sizing, I recommend sticking with what the size chart indicates but if you do prefer a looser fit for more of a bra top vibe, you can always size up! 

That all being said, a cool thing about fabric is that different colour dyes actually hold weight differently - often times fabrics dyed darker will feel heavier and tighter than lighter colour fabrics which may feel stretchier and lighter! Case and point: our super pigmented Eggplant feels a little heavier and tighter than the Sage. It’s a subtle difference but something to consider if you’re between sizes or sensitive to compression! The more you know, eh? 🤗

Okay, so we’re trying something brand new for this upcoming launch. And truth be told this is going to be a learning process so I appreciate your patience as we figure this out together!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Before I get into it, a little backstory. As a small business, Instagram has been an instrumental part of our growth. It’s been a great place to build relationships and a community. But as I’m sure you’ve heard a lot of your favourite creators and brands say, lately it’s just not the same. The algorithm is ever-changing, always tricky, and fewer people are seeing our posts. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
All this to say that every time we close a collection launch, we get a good handful of messages from folks saying that they didn’t see our posts, didn’t know a launch had happed and now the pieces they wanted are sold out or pre-orders closed. This doesn’t feel good on either end and while we also send out emails, we get how easily that can get lost in your inbox or get flagged as spam.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So… we thought we’d give text a try! And we want to do this in a way that’s helpful and promise not to send you too many. In any sort of messaging we put out, I always ask myself - would I want to receive this and is this helpful? If the answer is no, then we won’t send it! Plus in full transparency sending texts in Canada is expensive so we really won’t be sending a lot out 😂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our goal with texting is to send you the reminder that you don’t want to miss and nothing more. If this sounds like something that you’ve been wanting, sign up is linked in our bio!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
P.S. - text subscribers will get extra EXTRA early access to the March 21st launch at 4:00 pm PST! Email subscribers will get access 15 minutes later and then it opens to everyone at 5:00 pm PST. Since this is an in-stock launch, those extra 15 minutes can make a difference ;) 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Here's the thing about dresses. I love them, I really do. They make getting dressed simple and it's an easy way to immediately feel *put together* with a one and done. But... I have a hard time adding them to my wardrobe. 

Maybe it's the association left over from the days where I felt like I had to purchase a new outfit for every event but I tend to put dresses in the "I'll probably only wear this a couple times a year" category. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So when it came time to design this Spring collection, I knew I wanted to include a dress that could be worn as much as your favourite pair of jeans. One that I could reach for when I’m in the rare mood to “dress up” but also to throw on with a pair of sandals to take on the day. I didn’t want it to be fussy - there’s nothing worse then putting on a great outfit only to feel like it needs to sit *just right* to look great. The dress had to look great at any angle (backward or forward) 😉
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Intoducing... THE TYLER DRESS. 
Here are a few of my favourite features!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
‣ Multi-tie: So far we've come up with nearly a dozen different ways to tie it and are still discovering more.

‣ Reversible: You know us, of course we had to make it reversible! You can choose the elgant highneck for times you want to dress it up or the lower scoop neck for a daytime look. 

‣Wrap style: The ties are perfect weight fluctuations. You can wrap them tight for a cinched waist or tie them loosely for shift dress look. Tie them in the front, back, or circled around. They’re also great for defining baby bumps!

‣ Modest side slit: To make walking easy and to add a lil *va va voom* to your look
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So what do ya think?? Is this a style that's been missing in your wardrobe??
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

All I need is 5 days of sun in a row and I am mentally in spring. With seasonal shift, comes spring cleaning! I’ve already done a deep clean of my kitchen, washing machines, and even under the fridge (I’m amazing, I know) but now that the weather is creeping into double digits, it’s time for the dreaded spring closet clean.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Every spring and fall I do a big closet clean. I take EVERYTHING out of my closet and drawers, wipe down/vacuum (clothes create a LOT of dust) and start sorting my clothing in piles. I have a pile for seasonal pieces I love and that fit well that get put into airtight Tupperware and stored in the attic for next season. Then I fold and put away the seasonless pieces that I love and fit. I’ll keep wearing those. Now for the tough part.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Whatever remaining is what I don’t reach for; items I love but need to be repaired or up-cycled or don’t fit any longer. This is where the real work comes in. It’s easy to throw all this in a bag and drop off at the local thrift store or donation bin. But 85% of clothing donations end up in the landfill… so be extra thoughtful and repair what you love so you can continue loving it. Launder and wait for the beginning of the season to donate or consign so there’s a better chance it goes to use. And the most sustainable way to clean out your closet? Avoid buying new things that won’t stand the test of time. Trying to get rid of clothing you don’t wear in a sustainable way is a sobering reminder to only buy what you love.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For me, that means items that will still fit and look great throughout body fluctuations. It means choosing fewer trendy and more timeless pieces. It means sticking to styles and silhouettes I feel confident in (not ones I aspire to want to wear). It means shopping with the intention of adding a lifetime item to my wardrobe so that each new season, my “get rid of” pile gets smaller and smaller.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Hope that helps! And happy spring cleaning ◡̈

#springcleaning #closetcleanout #slowfashion #responsibleshopping

The Reese Short was designed with a special emphasis on making sure it wears well on curvy bodies. Growing up, I had a difficult time finding shorts that fit over my hips but didn’t gape at the waist and had enough room for my generous thighs. If this sounds relatable to you, I think the Reese Short is exactly what you’ve been looking for.

I’m all too familiar with the struggle of being in between sizes with a larger hip-to-waist ratio. When it comes to Cotton Crepe sizing, this fabric has no stretch so it’s important to take a look at the garment measurements. You want to make sure that your body measurements fit *within* the garment measurements with at least 1” of ease. For example, if your hip is 50” you want the hip of the pant to be at least 51” or more. I always recommend going with your larger measurement and thanks to the wrap style and waist tie, it’s easy to adjust to your perfect fit!

The other night I was watching a retro SATC episode. The episode touched on such an interesting phenomenon: skinny jeans. No, not the slim leg denim, but rather that pair of pants you keep tucked away at the back of your closet that no longer fit, but you hope that one day they will.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I can certainly relate to this (many of us can I’m sure). I remember keeping my HIGH SCHOOL jeans for nearly 5 years until I realized I will probably never wear them again. It took me another 5 years to realize I never need to. It took me another 5 to finally give up this toxic habit.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We’re raised by dieting parents and grandparents. Constantly reminded that gaining weight is a failure. Sizing up is a devastation. We hold this self depreciating trauma with us our whole lives. And one of the ways it manifests is in anxiety about clothing, fit and sizes. It manifests into the hope of holding onto those skinny jeans in case they fit one day and you can rip that “failure” label off yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I want to remind you that bodies are not inherently bad or good. That bodies are MEANT to change. That if we didn’t change and grow and shift and sag, we aren’t really in tune with the very nature of living.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And now, I want to remind you that you can sell that old, ill-fitting garment. That you can buy one that actually fits. That you can release yourself of the burden of upholding the impossible and infuriating belief that our smallest or most youthful bodies are the only ones worth celebrating.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I want to remind you that clothes are meant to fit bodies. Bodies aren’t meant to fit clothes. (Easier said than believed... but every reminder brings us closer to finally shifting this mindset).

#myfreelabel #bodyneutrality #celebratechange #bodypositivity

There's something about swimwear that makes me feel incredibly vulnerable. In fact, I believe it's a powerful act of self-love to put on a bathing suit and say "I feel great in this."
 
My goal with Free Label Swim is for you to put on these pieces and feel good inside and out, and more than anything, for these suits to make you feel like *you.*
 
In light of the upcoming Free Label swim restock (more on that below), I wanted to talk about fit. Swimwear is different from our everyday pieces. The fabric and fit are a lot more technical and with that comes unique considerations. When it comes to compression, it's normal for your swim pieces to feel extra snug on the first try and in fact, that's a good thing! If you can slip more than a finger between your suit and body, it may be too loose. When it comes to choosing your size, I recommend taking a look at the knit and bra size charts. We've found that folks who are in between sizes or don't like a lot of compression have chosen to size up. 
 
Our swim has been designed to not just look pretty in, but also to be moved in. It's meant to be worn time and time again, get wet, rinse, and repeat. We wanted to make sure that these swimsuits feel secure and don't slip off your body while swimming after seasons of wear (no one likes a saggy swim booty). You can expect a break-in period of 3-7 wears in water before the swim pieces fully relax and mould to your body like a second skin. We've also put together a blog post with a few tips on how to speed up the break-in process which is linked in our bio.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For folks who have received their suits, could you do us a favour and share your fit tips below (or by leaving a review on the product page) to help others out? 🙏

Have you ever gone to put something on your body when all of the sudden you hear that dreaded *pop* sound? You hear threads breaking as you wiggle into a garment and you think to yourself, oh no… 😰

Fear not, this isn’t *always* the product of low quality sewing - and in the case of many swimwear and activewear garments, it’s quite the opposite! Synthetic fabrics have a tendency to be quite slippery, so oftentimes sewers will add a “stay stitch” to the garment prior to sewing, to help keep the panels in place! This makes sewing cleaner, more accurate, and less frustrating 😉

The challenge with a stay stitch is that it does add extra tightness and compression to seams! So if you just received your Free Label swim and find the leg holes to be a bit tight, try giving them a tug to break that stay stitch and loosen them up!

We know it can be tricky deciding on a bathing suit so we wanted to share a couple other tips to break-in your suit if you’re worried it might be a little snug. 

Similarly to our bras, Free Label Swim pieces have a break-in period of 3-7 wears - but in water - before they fully relax and mould to your body like a second skin. If you’re looking to speed up this process, one of the things you can do it to snap the stay stitching. Some other things you can do to speed up the break-in process include taking a shower in your swimsuit (sounds silly but why wait for a beach day to come to you lol) or just wearing it around the house as you move around. All of this helps to relax the fabric and mould to your body.

If you’re not sure whether your suit fits, try squeezing a finger in the suit - if you can squeeze a finger in, it’s perfect and will relax to a comfortable fit. If you can fit more than a couple fingers than it’s too big and may sag overtime once fully relaxed.

The more ya know 😉

Enter: the Dani TANK. Modelled after our #1 best-selling bra, The Dani Tank is a perfect base layer compression tank with soft and subtle built-in support so even L cups can go braless! Lately, I've seen posts about the hazardous chemicals found in Shien clothing circulating again… but news like this sadly comes as no surprise. When it comes to fast fashion, it's easy to get drawn into the low-cost, high-dopamine cycle of consumption. I know I certainly did when I was younger. It gives you instant satisfaction - you see it, you want it, you buy it, you repeat. It’s now easier than ever before. But when you hear reports of how it can be a danger to your health - and the health of those who make the garments - it's hard to ignore the heavy reality of fast fashion.

We watched @riverbluethemovie at the office the other day and Mark Angelo summed it up perfectly. The reality is that "low-cost clothing has a high cost attached to it, one to the environment and public health". In the doc, he shows us the direct impact that the fashion industry has in places like China, India, and Bangladesh. How water sources essential to life in these places are so polluted that they are considered biologically dead - and yet the people living in the area still rely on them. How in Kanpur, this polluted water is still used for irrigation and every family has at least one person that has been affected by a skin condition as a result. How the tanneries in Bangladesh offer no protective wear to their workers yet the chemicals are heavy in the air and now there are kids in the area that no longer have a sense of smell. How they say you can guess the "it" colour of the season by seeing what colour the river has been dyed.

As a consumer, it's easy to not think about our purchase beyond how it affects us personally. Watching River Blue was a good reminder to think bigger. To not just ask myself, "Do I need this?" "Will I wear this for years to come?". But to also think about how my purchase aligns with my values. To think about where the clothes come from. And the impact each purchase has on the people that make them.

#riverbluethemovie #fastfashiondetox #slowfashionmovement

One of the biggest struggles of running a small business is production planning and estimating demand. It's a fine line between wanting a full website for folks to shop from with ease, while at the same time ensuring we never overproduce or create waste. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Over the years our comfy bamboo bras are what we have become known for. And as such, are the pieces we have the hardest time keeping in stock regularly! (Thanks for being as obsessed with them as we are 😙).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
While we wish there was a simple solution to this, it's important to us that we engage in responsible production, minimize waste, and make sure that we don't carry overstock. This is also why before an in-stock launch of popular items, we typically start with a pre-order. So you can get exactly what you want without worrying about selling out!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
All this to say that the wait is finally over, bra production has wrapped up, pre-orders have been shipped, and a restock will be landing on May 26.

Why is shopping for a swimsuit one of the most frustrating things?? We all have the experience of trying on loads of ill fitting suits in a cramped change room (where the only mirror is outside of the room next to the pushy sales person 😫). 

The fit of a swimsuit is integral to its function and your confidence as the wearer. You don’t want it to be too loose or your bottoms will fly off post-cannonball. And you don’t want it to be too small so that you feel uncomfortable in public. I needs to be *just right*. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Being a firm believer that clothes should fit you and not the other way around, we created a swim suit that you can design for youself to suit you and your body! We all have different shapes, sizes, proportions and coverage needs. The Saturna Swim Top is reversible and multi-tie and accommodates bust of all shapes and sizes with it’s endless tie options. The Bowen Bottom is also reversible and has adjustable side ties for your ideal amount of coverage.
 
We made it so that YOU could design it ❤️ 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
What’s your favourite way to wear our two piece??

When I first started being more mindful of my consumption and curating a wardrobe full of items that I get a lot of wear out of, it was the pieces that I love but only wear once or twice a year that I struggled the most with. Typically, these were “special occasion” dresses. The ones I felt like I could only wear when I was dressing up or going to an event.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So when it came time to design a dress, I knew I wanted something that could could become a closet staple rather than a once a year try on. A dress I could wear to a fancy event and that I could wear with sneakers while running errands. One that I could wear both loose-fitting and body-hugging. With an elegant high neck and a more casual scoop neck. All while being uber comfortable (because let’s get real. That is the number one priority). And thus, the Tyler Dress was born! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Many times this spring, I’ve been getting dressed and thought to myself, “The Isabel Tank would have been perfect for this outfit”. But it sold out so quickly last time that I didn’t even have time to snag one for myself! 🥲

The Isabel Tank is the perfect sleeveless version of the versatile Isabel Wrap Top. It’s a 20-in-one type of top that can be worn in endless ways and is always exactly what you need it to be. From body-hugging to a loose fit, modest high neck to a sultry v-neck, full length to under the bust, it truly can do it ALL. It’s just up to your creativity!

There are times I wish we had a storefront because there are some pieces that if you could try out first hand you would *get it* as soon as it was on your body. The Rai Crop is definitely one of those styles. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
At our Toronto pop-up, there were many folks who hadn't come in with the intent of trying on the Rai Crop but would see them while browsing and say "Well if I'm here, I may as well try them on!". And seeing so many bodies wear the Rai Crop was pure magic. They look great on EVERY BODY. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
What’s special about the Rai Crop is the effortless silhouette that delicately drapes over your body and the side slit that gives you the breezy ease of a skirt or shorts but in PANT form. They're comfortable enough for your most relaxing days (lounging on the couch and going for a stroll in your neighbourhood) and chic enough for dressier occasions too (diner dates and even weddings).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Don't just take my word for it though, if you've tried on the bamboo Rai Crop and love it as much as we do, leave a little love note in the comments! We love to read them - and I know other community members do too!!

The SS23 Bamboo collection launches on Thursday, June 22 at 3:00 pm PST. SMS and email subscribers get an hour of early access! The Rai Crop will be available in Umber, Sage, Forest, and Black in sizes 5X-XS.

#raicrop #pantsforeverybody #culottes #myfreelabel #slowfashionmovement

Introducing... THE SONNY BRA
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
One of the superpowers of small business is that *you* have a direct impact on the styles we design. At the beginning of the year, we asked the community on our Facebook group, what their dream bra would look like and an overwhelming amount of you had the same suggestion... A summer version of the Dani Bra! A bra with the beloved crossover front but with a low scoop back to mitigate feeling sticky and sweaty in the warmer months. And so that is exactly what we did.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
While we designed this piece to be non-reversible, many folks CAN reverse depending on your bust size/shape/coverage preferences. So *officially* it’s non-reversible, but you can be the judge! 😉
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This limited quantity summer special will come in Black, Eggplant, Forest Sage, Umber and... 2 colours that we haven’t had in a while *drumroll please* Clay and Storm!!
 
When it comes to fit, I know a lot of folks like to size up for the Dani bra, due to its compressive nature. The low back of the Sonny Bra means that it’s less compressive so I recommend going with your typical Free Label bra size. The compression is comparable to the Becky Bra for reference.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So what do you think?? Is it everything you dreamed it would be?? If you have any questions about this upcoming launch, pop them below!

Introducing... The Zero Waste Tote! 
Remember our luscious Cotton Twill from a few seasons ago? Instead of throwing out (we could never!!) the leftover roll ends and offcuts like many bigger brands do, we've been hanging on to them and brainstorming what to make out of it. We knew we wanted it to be useful and functional and so... we made tote bags!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It's the perfect size to hold everything you need with a zippered interior pocket for easy access to your essentials such as keys and wallet. It has a magnet closure to safeguard your belongings and a sturdy shoulder strap so you really fill up your tote without worrying about it being too heavy! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I've been getting SO much use out of it already and hope you will too! 💓 Plus, not a bad way to get your cart up to our free shipping minimum 😉

#zerowaste #offcutfashion #slowfashionmovement #sustainablefashion

Now that it actually FEELS like summer in Vancouver, I’ve switched over my wardrobe to tuck away cold weather pieces and bring out breezy summer items. And you know what? Almost all my bamboo stayed. We love an all season textile 👏

Our bamboo is not only substantial and soft for the winter months, but bamboo is naturally temperature regulating (keeping you cool in summer), antibacterial (so it doesn’t get stinky after a sweaty season of wear) and easy to fit (even after a season of body changes!).

The Sonny Bra, Rai Crop, and Isabel tank aren’t the only versatile bamboo pieces we have on the site right now though. Not a huge fan of sleeveless tops? May I suggest the OG Isabel Wrap Top that the tank version was based off of? It has flowy Stevie Nicks inspired sleeves that drape away from the armpit perfect for breezy summer nights and endless tie options. On the hunt for shorts? The Sarah Short has an ultra high waistband and a longer inseam, it’s the ultimate anti-chafe solution. You can wear it on its own or layer under skirts and dresses! This is one of those pieces you do laundry FOR - it’s hard to go a couple summer days without my Sarah Shorts!

What’s your go-to outfit now that it’s officially summer??

#summerstyle #bamboofabric #slowfashionsummer #slowfashionmovement

I used to feel like I wasn’t meant to wear shorts. It’s rare that I find pair that fits well, makes me feel good, and is designed for my shape. It took years of unlearning to internalize that I shouldn’t have to fit *into* the shorts but that the shorts should fit *me*. 

The wrap style of the Reese Shorts has been perfected over the years (the OG Reese Pant launched in 2018!) and is designed to celebrate your unique shape. It has long ties that allow you to always achieve your perfect waist fit through weight fluctuations and body changes. It’s roomy in the hips and has a privacy panel in the front to work with different body proportions. Not to mention the inseam that’s just long enough to prevent chafing and a generously cut leg designed for thicker legs (we deserve a little drape too!).

In short (haha get it?), these are the shorts I was dreaming of back when I felt like shorts weren’t for me but reaaaally wished they could be.

If you’ve had these feelings before, I hope that our Reese Short are a perfect solution for your short woes! Have you tried them? What do you think?

The Cotton Crepe restock is on Thursday, July 6 at 10:00 am PST. Email and SMS subscribers get an hour of early access. The Reese Short will be available in Black, Eucalyptus, and Navy in sizes 5X-XS.

It’s not often that we bring back the same pieces 3 TIMES in one season but if that’s not a testament to how well-loved the Loretta Pant is, I don’t know what is!

The Loretta Pant is the perfect everyday pant. A pant that can be worn through every season, for every occasion, and can be styled with nearly everything in your closet. The wide leg and high waist with a soft elastic waistband create an effortlessly elegant silhouette that is the perfect mix of timeless and on trend. For the days you want something more structured than loungewear but not as rigid as denim, the Loretta Pant is exactly what you’re looking for.

They’re like cute pajamas that you can wear for real world stuff. 😉

Button-ups have always been one of my most worn pieces. They’re so incredibly versatile not only in how many ways they can be styled but in how many roles it fills in my closet. 

On days I want to look more put together, I button it up and wear it as a work top. When it’s not quite jacket weather but I’m feeling a little chilly, it’s the perfect layering piece. When I want to dress down a fancier outfit or cover up my arms, I throw a button-up over the top and the look always comes together. At the beach, it’s the perfect cover-up for when I need sun protection over my suit. I wear it over short skirts, dresses, and shorts when I need 🍑 coverage. In colder weather, I layer it under sweaters with the collar sticking out for warmth and a fun way to accessorize. All this to say that a great button-up is truly the definition of a wardrobe essential to me. 

And if you’re wondering what makes the Tommy Button-Up my favourite button-up? Just watch the reel 😉

Are button-ups a wardrobe essential for you too? 

The Cotton Crepe restock is on Thursday, July 6 at 10:00 am PST. Email and SMS subscribers get an hour of early access. The Tommy Button-Up will be available in Black, Ivory, and Navy in sizes 5X-XS.

#buttonup #versatilewardrobe #slowfashion #tommybuttonup

Sometimes I find that the most “basic” items are the hardest to find. Like a white tee that’s the exact shape you were looking for and isn’t see-through. Or a skirt that skims your body in just the right way and is the ideal length. Or say.. a no-frills basic tank top that fits just so. This is the vision we had for the Millie Tank. 

After multiple samples of tank tops with bells and whistles like ties and open backs, we realized that that wasn’t what you were looking for so we went back to the basics. The Millie Tank is a simple timeless top with careful attention to detail to design the *perfect* fit. 

•A classic scoop neck that’s not too low and not too high
•Sleeveless but can we worn without the worry of bra straps
•A gentle timeless curved hem 
•A length perfect for tucking into high-rise pants and offers enough coverage for mid-rise
•Darts for a better bust fit and reduced gaping in the armpits
•Binding in the neckline and armhole for more structure

So what do you think??

The Cotton Crepe restock is on Thursday, July 6 at 10:00 am PST. Email and SMS subscribers get an hour of early access. The Millie Tank will be available in Black, Eucalyptus, and Navy in sizes 5X-XS.

#basictank #tanktop #cottoncrepe #cottonclothing #millietank #slowfashion

Do you have enough stuff? Can you afford to shop elsewhere?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
These can be the first questions you ask yourself before participating in pr!me day. I know how easy it can be to get swept up in the mindset of finding the deals. But the things is, deals are only a good deal when the items you’re purchasing are something you truly need. If you don’t have a predetermined list of *essentials* that you could really use a discount on (times are tough, I get it), then please don’t spend hours scrolling am@zon trying to find a deal that you probably don’t need.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We all know how shitty the company is. There are plenty of articles and reports out there telling us the stories. How workers are underpaid, overworked and in unsafe environments. How the executive team gets paid thousands of times more than the median employee. We know their strategy to incentivize workers to quit so they can hire new, cheaper labourers in order to keep costs low. We know the owner is (or was recently) the richest person in the world. We already know all of this.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But we also know that we live under capitalism. And times are tough right now. Many families are struggling to survive the wild cost of living in a world where the gap between the poor and the rich keeps getting wider. So if that’s you, I’m not telling you to avoid pr!me day. But have the self awareness to know if that really IS you, or whether you’re trying to justify that cheap purchase/dopamine hit. Because someone else IS paying for your savings: like the warehouse worker and the product manufacturer. So if you do have the means, please don’t perpetuate the cycle of poverty if you have a choice.

#ethicallabour #sustainability

1. Keep in mind that once you wax, you can’t go back! The wax will give your garment a worn-in look and change the colour a bit.

3. Work in small circles and don’t try to cover a big surface area in one go

HOW TO MEASURE YOUR US BRA SIZE AT HOME ✨

I get it, shopping for bras online can be tricky. But the good news is that we’ve worked really hard on our bra size chart to help you find your perfect fit! Now, the bra size chart only makes sense if you know your bra size and let’s be honest, it may have been a while (I think I was still in high school...) since you last got your bra size measured. But there’s good news again! It’s really easy to do it yourself at home and all you need is a measuring tape. 

Step 1: Grab a measuring tape. For the most accurate measurements, you want to do this without a bra on

Step 2: Take your bust measurement. You want to make sure that you’re measuring over the fullest part of your bust and that the measuring tape is parallel to the floor

Step 3. Take your band measurement by measuring right under your bust. This is the band number that comes before your cup letter.

Step 4: Math time! Subtract your band measurement from your bust measurement. 

Step 5: Use the number from above to calculate your cup size! Each cup letter increases with each inch. Use the chart on our story (and saved to highlights) to find this out. 

And there you have it! Now you know your band and cup size and you can use this with our bra size chart to find your perfect FL fit. Ooh, and one more thing! If your band measurement is an uneven number, round down to the nearest even number. *voila*

If you have any questions or need help with calculating, leave a comment or drop us a DM :) 

P.S. If you’ve been thinking of getting a FL bra, this information may come in handy very soon 👀

Did you know how to measure your bra size? Hope this was helpful!

I started Free Label over 8 years ago and since then this company has been my little baby. I love what I do, the amazing folks I get to work with, and this special FL community SO MUCH. I really am so lucky. 💓

I’ve been known to be an oversharer - Ive tried to take you on some of my personal journeys throughout the years, because I know that despite our different paths we are all ultimately living through common experiences. And what better way to feel seen and acknowledged than to share some of what you’re going through with someone else.

You saw the ups and downs of starting this small business. You witnessed the making of the dress I wore to my wedding and then auctioned off for charity. You read my deepest thoughts and emotions throughout a global pandemic. You followed along as I hired the incredible FL team and moved into an office and warehouse space. You’ve been there through it all!

Lately I’ve been shying away from sharing my personal life with you all. I thought long and hard about whether I would talk about this next chapter of my life, and decided that it would be too hard to hide it (you know I love a sneak peek/spoiler 😂). This collection started with a list (of years in the making) of all our denim woes. This list fuelled our design process and inspired us to create the denim pieces of our dreams. When I asked about your denim woes, it turned out that your woes were our woes.

Your most common denim woe by far, (I would say about 90% of the messages we received) was about fit. More specifically, the hip-to-waist ratio fit and feeling like you’re always left with a waist gap to accommodate your hips. This is exactly what we’re trying to fix with our fit. We did a lot of fit testing to come up with a design that eliminates the gap at the back of the waist for a tailored fit while having ample room for your hips. Win-win!

Next up was feel. You want to feel comfortable in denim and so do we. This is why it was important to us to find a quality denim with stretch. If you missed our post yesterday about the fabric, be sure to check that out for all the deets! I’ve worn our denim samples for hours; sitting at the office and running errands, and it’s always been A+ in comfort for me. And if the fact that Jess has worn her Denim Stevie skirt through pregnancy and can still comfortably sit in it to this day isn’t a true indicator of stretch and comfort, I don’t know what is 😂

We hope that for all you denim skeptics out there, this changes your mind like it did ours. And for all you denim lovers, we hope this becomes the next well-worn pair in your closet. 😉

And of course, we couldn't forget about tops. No, we're not talking denim tops because we could never do that better than Britney and JT. So instead, we have 2 cozy organic cotton + lyocell tops that go with absolutely everything. 

I can’t wait for you to meet all these pieces in the coming days. Which piece do you want to hear all about first?? 💕

LETS TALK ABOUT FIT! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Online shopping can be hard and some pieces feel harder than others, denim being one of them. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is why when designing this denim capsule, our top priority was to find a quality stretch denim fabric that allows flexibility in sizing and throughout weight fluctuations. Case in point, I've been wearing the same size L throughout pregnancy as my waist has gone from 32" to 38"!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
While many people can toggle between two sizes, here are a few fit tips to help you choose your best size on the first try:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
▫️Prioritize your waist measurement - the waistband has fusing inside which gives it a bit more stability, but reduces stretch
▫️If you missed the collection preview, take a look at our denim highlight for garment measurements - since these are stretch pieces, you’ll want your body measurements to be the same or slightly larger than the garment measurements (aka negative ease)
▫️The Stevie Skirt has been designed to have more of a structured fit with thicker fusing in the waist so be mindful of looking at the difference between the Stevie Skirt and Pant measurements if you're interested in both - if you’re in between waist sizes for the Skirt you may want to consider sizing up
▫️While the denim pieces are wovens, they do have added stretch so you can consider BOTH the woven and knit size charts depending on your ideal fit. These pieces are flexible!
▫️Take a look at the try-ons we have saved in our denim highlight to see if you can find a body twin!
▫️Think about your intention for this new wardrobe addition: Do you expect to go through body changes soon? Do you want a slouchy comfy fit or a slim fit? This may help you decide whether to size up or down.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And like always, we accept returns within 7 days on unworn purchases (plus our Facebook group is a great way to swap sizes in a pinch). Let’s find your perfect denim fit ◡̈

In the meantime I’d love to know… what are you pet peeves with traditional “activewear”?

#comingsoon #slowfashionmovement #movementwear

Before I started Free Label, I was in the activewear world. I managed an activewear boutique in Toronto and then moved to Vancouver and did marketing at a locally made activewear brand before eventually quitting my full-time gig for Free Label. Throughout my years of experience in the activewear niche, I always ran into the same ol problems and judging from yesterday’s post, so have you!

-activewear typically is made for straight sizes only or at least FIT TESTED on size S models with plus sizes being an afterthought with grading. This results in poor curve fit (loose waistbands, tight calves… IYKYK)
-fabric felt cheap, super plasticy and you had to choose between thin and soft fabric that doesn’t compress or stay up, or highly compressive “crunchy” fabric that doesn’t move with your body. And my biggest pet peeve? TRANSPARENT FABRIC 😤 Why would I want strangers seeing my underwear while I’m squatting?!?!
-activewear is designed to be so casual that it lacks versatility in your wardrobe: unnecessary style lines, visible branding, contrast stitching all make it so you can’t dress up that perfect pair of black leggings
-off the rack sports bras are NEVER made for D+ cups. As a humble B cup I often found myself spilling out of sports bras during any activity, which begs the question - what do the vast majority of boob-owners wear?!

Naturally, I've always kept activewear on my mind. But because I’m SO picky and particular, it’s taken me 8 (!!!) years to finally create my own capsule. We’ve been working on the fit, fabric and function of these pieces for YEARS and my hope is that they solve the issues we’ve  seen time and time again in the industry. 

Introducing… Free Label’s first ✨MOVEMENT CAPSULE✨ A second skin in sizes 5X-XS to support whatever movement feels good to you. Whether it’s yoga, gymming, walking, or stretching. Hell, even getting up to grab a bag of chips from the kitchen. WE’VE GOT YOU!

✨ THE MOVEMENT SARAH SHORT ✨
It's everything you love about the OG Bamboo Sarah Short with a few edits that make it perfect for movement of any type and... it's squatproof!! 

First up, what you already know and love about the Sarah Short:
▫️ An intentionally designed leg that has been shaped so it lays flat on thighs of many sizes. (No digging in!) 

▫️An inseam long enough to prevent uncomfortable chafing

▫️ A high-rise waistband that feels comfy and secure. When I asked about your "activewear" pet peeves,  #1 on the list was pants that roll down. This is why the Sarah Short has been designed with an extra wide waistband that slightly tapers in at the waist so that it curves to your body. The wider waistband also helps with the distribution of compression and theres a very light elastic structure to keep everything nice and secure while not feeling pinchy!

And now for the edits that make it perfect for movement:

Whenever I describe what ‘type’ of clothing we make at Free Label, I have difficulty categorizing it as one thing. What I end up saying is that we design comfortable everyday clothing. Pieces that make you feel good and also feel good ON your body. Styles that you can wear with nearly everything in your existing wardrobe and that make getting dressed easy, because who needs another daily stress?
 
When designing this collection, we challenged ourselves to create the ultimate ‘Free Label Starter Pack’. A variety of styles that fill gaps in different areas of your wardrobe. Comfy cozy bamboo undergarments (including perhaps the return of an old favourite), buttery soft pants to match, and a top layer to tie it all together.

We’re unlocking the vault with the comeback (finally!!! 😭) of a fan-favourite style that was first designed in 2016...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✨THE SUNDAY CROP✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This design was born out of the desire to wear sweatpants all the time but craving something more chic, elevated and versatile. We kept the aspects we love most about sweats (comfortable and loose fit) and upgraded everything else! Let me tell you more 😉
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Starting at the top, we ditched the drawstring and harsh elastic for an ultra-high roll-down waistband. You can wear the band folded down or all the way up. I’ve always said that this is a popular style for mama before, during, and after pregnancy and now I’ve actually been able to put that to the test through my own pregnancy. And let me tell you… I CANNOT LIVE WITHOUT MY SUNDAYS. They still fit like a dream, are so comfy and are easy to style with things I already wear (and still fit into).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Next up, I’ve always found the tummy area of sweats to be ill-fitting with no intentional design. And so we added pleats below the waistband that flow over your curves and maintain an effortless drape.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
To finish things off, we designed a shaped leg and added ruching to the bottom to make it a great fit for a variety of inseam lengths!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And the fabric, we can’t forget that! One of the things I find that can make sweatpants feel like “home only” clothes is when the fabric pills after just a couple washes. Enter our infamous custom-milled buttery soft bamboo fabric. It stands the test of time and after years of washes, my Sunday Crops are still going strong! Anyone wanna hop in the comments and vouch for this too?? 😘
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

This may be controversial, but I’m a firm believer that a great legging is a wardrobe *essential*. Now hear me out, leggings sometimes get a bad rep but they’re one of my worst-worn pieces of clothing, year round!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. They’re a fantastic transition piece. When it’s in between seasons, I like to elongate the life of my summer clothes (like skirts) by layering leggings underneath
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. They’re a great baselayer in the winter months. To keep extra toasty, I like to wear leggings under pants like the Loretta. Pair with fluffy socks and a good boot and you’re ready to take on the cold! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. Say it with me now: 👏LEGGINGS👏ARE👏PANTS👏! Paired with a FL bra for a matching set moment and layered with a sweater or trench, I think they make for a pretty great (and comfy) outfit.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But there are tons of leggings out there. So why did we make the Robson? We wanted a super high-waisted, full length, and simple seamless design that could easily elevate the legging look. Plus our bamboo is so soft and silky - if you’re one of those people (like me) that get itchy with certain legging fabrics, these will be your go to.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So what do you think... are leggings pants? I personally and wholeheartedly vote YES. If you’re looking for legging inspo - how to style them or how to wear them *not* as pants, take a look at our story :)

Here is a breakdown of the Andie, Carrie, and Dani bras!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Andie Bra: Our first ever and best-selling bra. You can wear this ultra-comfy bra in two different ways: with an elegant high neckline or a sultry v-neck. This bra has a shorter cup than the others: great for giving shape and lift to smaller busts. It's best suited for cup sizes AA-DD.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Carrie Bra: If you're looking for a lower coverage option that's great for layering, this is it! The Carrie is compressive and has great cup coverage for small to big busts, with bust separating ruching and adjustable not-too-thin straps. The Carrie is best suited for cup sizes AA-G. If you’re in between sizes, some folks choose to size up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Dani Bra: A unicorn bra for those with heavier chests. It's the most compressive of our bra styles and has deep cups to accommodate full busts. The deep-v crossover side offers bust separation and it's great for nursing mamas. You can also wear it high neck forward for extra coverage. The Dani is best suited for cup sizes D-L! If you’re in between sizes, some folks choose to size up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

From the start, Free Label has been about finding comfort and function in clothing, all while maintaining sustainable and ethical practices. Building a new wardrobe from scratch every time you go through a size change or life event is just not realistic. And it’s definitely no fun.

Something I’m proud of, is how people DM all the time and share that they’ve been able to wear their FL pieces throughout pregnancy and postpartum, through weight loss or gain, and even through serious shifts in health (for example, our bras have been said to bring comfort to folks going through mastectomy recovery). I know slow fashion can sometimes come with sticker shock. But keep in mind longevity! High quality and easy fit/well designed pieces can support you through many eras of your life. And hopefully one day be passed along to someone else like a favourite heirloom.

So anyways, this is a reel showing how I am still wearing all my fav Free Label pieces at 35 weeks pregnant because I ain’t buying expensive maternity clothes that I’ll wear for a handful of months. No siree.

If you’ve worn your FL throughout different shifts and stages of your life, I’d love to hear your story! ❤️

From a design perspective, working with patterns is hard. It’s one of the reasons we typically stick with solid colours because when we do print, we want to make sure we’re doing it right! 

The thing about print fabric is that it has to be cut and sewn in a *very* specific way to make sure that everything lines up in the final product. This tedious task is the difference between say, a designer bag where all the seams line up perfectly, and a cheap knock off. It costs time and money to be THIS precise.

And when it’s comes to a wrap pant style like the Reese with an extra privacy panel, well,  you can imagine how complicated this can get. But, our technical pattern designer and production partners did *such* an amazing job cutting and sewing the pieces so everything matches up *perfectly* for a seamless fit. Even on Jess who’s currently 36 weeks pregnant (!!) 

To us, it’s the small design details that make a biiig difference 😙👌🏼 wouldn’t you say?

6. It has a built in shelf bra! And if you’d like some extra support, we designed the neckline to accommodate a variety of straps without it peeking out.

My body has been going through a lot of rapid changes over the past few months. And something I’ve noticed about rapid body changes - whether it’s due to pregnancy, weight loss or gain, health changes, etc- is that it can create an identity crisis. When I look at my passing reflection in a store window, I hardly recognize myself. It’s quite the out-of-body experience to feel your mind and your body disconnect like that. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ve found that being able to continue wearing my usual clothing has greatly helped me stay grounded in my body, recognize and connect with myself, and find acceptance. I’m 9 months pregnant and still haven’t had to buy any maternity-specific clothing. 🤟 I’ve continued wearing my usual comfy bamboo and elastic waistband pieces while my waist grew 10+ inches (not to mention the changes to my bewbs, hips, etc). Of course, that’s not only been a financial relief but has also helped me avoid having to re-establish my personal style at a time when I feel like I’m slowly floating away from the identity I know.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I still have trouble recognizing myself in the mirror but at least the person I’m looking at has the same cute style I’ve become familiar with ;)

You probably already know... but we are not having a Black Friday sale this year. And here is why.
 
Shopping can feel like a sport. The fear of missing out spurs a race to find the best deals as you rush to the finish line to checkout before time runs out. Black Friday serves to amplify this. And you have to wonder… how much of the stuff purchased on BF is still being worn/used today. How much of it has ended up at the landfill?

Now don’t get me wrong, I’m not saying don’t buy anything this BFCM. Times are tough and as the cost of living rises, this can be an opportunity to stock up on necessities at a lower price point. But more often, the greater amount spent is on things we wouldn’t have otherwise bought, all in the name of a tempting sale.

We believe shopping should always be an intentional practice. And this is why once again, we are choosing to forgo a Black Friday sale, and instead go #BeyondBlackFriday to redistribute our potential BF sales to BIPOC-owned business. Why? Because, ironically, we want to SAVE you money. We want you to make mindful decisions and not feel the pressure to buy something just because it's on sale. Because, quite frankly, our items don't have the margins for discounts (It's expensive to make things ethically, locally, and sustainably.) Because even though it feels like people have stopped talking about the importance of shopping BIPOC-owned, it’s as important as ever. And the world of business still needs a redistribution of wealth and resources.

So if it’s in your capacity, we encourage you to go into Black Friday mindfully and take a portion of your savings to pay it forward. Next week on Black Friday we’ll raise money for BIPOC-owned small businesses and sell raffle tickets with 100% of the proceeds going to the Empowerful Incubator Fund. As a bonus, you’ll be entered to win prizes valued at $1500!!!! (A win-win!). Last year with your support, we raised $4500 and with our $10,000 contribution, the Free Label community was able to distribute $14,500 to multiple BIPOC small-business owners to help grow their brands. This year our goal is to raise $5000 for a total of $15,000.
 
This year, will you go #BeyondBlackFriday?

Come behind the scenes on how the Long-Sleeve Jules Dress and Denim Stevie Pant came to be! ✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 1: A major perk of small biz? We hear your requests! After the launch of the OG Jules Dress and then skirt, we had many requests for a long-sleeve version! As for denim, this one was on our goals list for a looooong time after realizing that we all share a lot of common denim woes. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 2: We meet with our pattern maker to discuss grading and start designing so we can make our first samples. While industry grading rules typically cater to straight sizes, we’ve crafted our own set of rules. This unique approach empowers us to tailor patterns for a diverse range of bodies and allows us to split patterns into straight and plus sizes if needed.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For example, industry standards would have us increase the length of the Jules Dress sleeve with every size and instead, we add length to the armhole, which provides a roomier fit without an excessively long sleeve. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 3: After receiving our initial samples, we dive into a thorough fit test, ensuring we cover a range of sizes to get feedback on fit and comfort and general thoughts on the piece. We then meet back up with our pattern maker to adjust and make new samples. This cycle continues until we have a garment that meets our standards and is exactly what we’ve been dreaming of. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For the Stevie Pant, we honed in on details like cinching the waist for a closer fit. Meanwhile, with the Long-Sleeve Jules Dress, we narrowed the scoop neck for versatile wear in the front or back and adjusted the sleeve length for that ideal touch.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 4: This brings us to today! After many months (The Jules and Stevie took about 6 each), we can confidently share the pieces with you 😊️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Movement hasn't always been a source of joy for me. As a kid, it seemed so effortless to incorporate into my life as a form of play and connection. Then as I entered young adulthood it changed. Movement became something I felt like I had to do so that maybe I could look like the bodies I saw in magazines and movies. Movement and working out became synonymous so I'd go to the gym and on long runs but it wasn't fun and always felt like a chore.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It took years of internal work to reframe this thought. I learned to be kind to myself, realizing that movement shouldn't feel like punishment. It should spark joy and feel good and it can look different for everyone. The goal isn't a specific body or number on the scale but rather feeling good *in* my body as it is.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our goal for this capsule is to celebrate the joy of movement, in whatever form it looks like for you. Whether it's a stroll around your neighbourhood, gentle stretching, moving around the house, your favourite workout class, or a dance party in your living room we're here to celebrate all of it. How do you like to move your body?
