New year… new you? 

This time of year, we’ve already started getting inundated with targeted ads fraught with messaging about resolutions and how so-and-so product will help you be ✨ the best version of yourself! ✨…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I started my career in activewear, and I can tell you from experience that the industry is riddled with body dysmorphia, fatphobia and toxic perceptions of health and wellness. I don’t think it’s malicious, I believe we’re all victims of these societal beliefs. But we can’t ignore that those nasty beliefs permeate into the product. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The belief that health and wellness = thinness means that most activewear is only made up to size L. It means most sports bras only accommodate up to C cups. It means leggings and shorts are designed for hard bodies and fit tested on very specific body proportions. It means the product will be exclusive, poor fitting and non-functional. And because of this, access to movement becomes exclusive too. But everyone deserves the right to explore joy in movement.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When we decided to venture into a movement-focused capsule, I knew it had to solve this problem. So we made sports bras that *finally fit* larger busted and chest-feeding folks, bottoms that actually stay up through movement and don’t cut into softer flesh, and cozy functional top layers that help you complete an outfit so you can justify wearing leggings and a sports bra all day ;)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We spent over a YEAR designing, testing and perfecting these pieces to ensure they have enough compression to be functional for your HIIT workout, but soft enough to support gentle stretches.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The movement capsule is NOW LIVE in limited quantities just in time for you to decide the same old you is actually just PERFECT for the new year. 💓

#movementwear #plussizeactivewear #notyouraverageactivewear #everybodymoves

My secret to making the most of my “lighter” wardrobe pieces year-round? Layering! 

Keeping warm outdoors while having the flexibility to shed layers and avoid overheating indoors? That’s a win in my book 💓

Here are a few tips I like to keep in mind:
▫️ Start with a snug, moisture-wicking base layer! This prevents that uncomfortable sweaty feeling while you stay warm 😅
▫️ The insulating layer is your key to retaining body heat. I personally love the coziness of a thin turtleneck.
▫️ Top it all off with your chosen outfit!

Steff is wearing denim and a light-knit sweater here which on its own might be a bit too chilly for December weather (even in Vancouver 😉) but with the layers underneath and a jacket to top it off, she’s good to go! 

What are your go-to layering tips? I’d love to hear your favourites!

#winterdressing #layeringclothing #slowfashionstyle #decemberootd

2023 has been… a really long year. 

On a business note: this has been our most challenging year ever. I try to stay positive and know everyone is struggling so I have shied away from so much, concerned it will come across as complaining. But you know I also have very little filter and would rather share my truth than pretend.The fact is, we are BURNT. OUT. We’ve spent the year busting our butts trying to create beautiful and functional new products that you will love. We’ve never made more new styles (and making new styles takes a LOT of time, effort and investment). But we’ve had no choice because it’s never been harder to reach new people. And without new customers, we have to focus on creating new things for our amazing existing customers to maintain our revenue and keep our team and spaces… This year has been SO much work, and it’s felt like we’re constantly running uphill and can’t quite get where we need to be. Free Label is all about sustainability, but this isn’t sustainable for us. All I can do is hope if we keep our heads down and do everything we can to make it, next year will be better.

On a personal note (because like I said, no filter) - 2023 was the most challenging of my life. I spent the majority of the year pregnant - which while it was a blessing, I struggled with the loss of myself. I wasn’t prepared for the demands on my body and my mind, and how confusing it is to feel like you’re meant to keep living life, working hard, being social, and doing the most, all while feeling like a shell of your previous self. Labour was also incredibly demanding on my body and mind. And as I write this with a two-week-old baby, learning life with a newborn is… yep, you guessed it, demanding on my body and mind! The rollercoaster of emotions accompanying this wild flux of hormones can be all-consuming. At the same time, I juggle guilt for not being there for my first baby: this business.

All to say 2023 has been A LOT. 

Through it all I’m still hopeful. So we’re going to do what we always do this time of year. But this time we’re going ALL. OUT.

Part of being in the slow fashion biz means that we never create a new design just because it’s “trendy” or it’s forecasted to be the next new and exciting thing. In fact, we want it to be quite the opposite of those things. It’s important to us that our designs are timeless and something you’ve already been wanting and will wear rather than something you’ve been persuaded to want because it’s “in.” (And let’s get real, those trendy items are often not aligned with your personal style and therefore don’t last in your closet past a season…)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Case in point, the Long-Sleeve Jules Dress! This piece initially started as a sleeveless dress that launched in the spring season a couple of years ago and after selling out immediately, we received constant requests for a long sleeve version. The Jules dress is so timeless, elegant, and easy to wear for different occasions (because we all have enough special occasion dresses sitting way in the back of the closet). You can wear it scoop neck forward for nights out, you can wear it high-neck forward for more formal events or work and when you’re looking for coverage, you can dress it down and wear it with sneakers and throw a shirt or sweater overtop. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Jules has become a Free Label fan favourite and… it just got added to the sale! Enjoy a discount until January 8th 😊️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Here’s a little #ThrowbackThursday to being 9 months pregnant at my maternity shoot (Is #TBT still a thing or am I aging myself here 🙃)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This photo was taken at 36 weeks and I still hadn’t purchased any maternity clothing! In fact throughout my pregnancy I did not purchase a single maternity piece and I definitely credit that to having a Free Label heavy wardrobe (to say the least). The Sunday Crop and Andie Bra were some of my most worn pieces from 1st trimester right up until going into labour (I wore an FL bra and the Sunday Crops the day I went into labour in fact!).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now that I’m half way through the fourth trimester and my body has changed YET AGAIN 😒 (holy moly it’s hard to keep up with the changes). I find myself continuing to reach for the clothing that gave me comfort during pregnancy. I no longer have my big belly but my waist has grown, my boobs have gotten bigger, and for some reason my butt has shrunk (???) and I still wear the exact same outfit AND feel great in it. Plus even though these pants stretched to accommodate my belly for nine months, they still fit like a dream! 🪄✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When designing clothing and choosing fabric, making pieces that don’t lose their place in my wardrobe after body changes is always top of mind. I don’t want to spend money or take on the mental burden of buying new clothing with every shift (and over the years there have been lots of shifts). So most Free Label pieces have some aspect of size flexibility built into the design 🤗
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Have you noticed the flexibility of sizing? Have your FL pieces carried you through different seasons of life? I’d love to know what your favourites are and what other versatile styles you’d like to see us make in the future! Personally, I’m thinking of more nursing friendly tops as we design for Fall 2024. What else??

The top *you* designed is back with the edits that *you* requested! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
At the beginning of last year, we introduced The Dani Tank, a style that was dreamt up by this community. There was a lot that you loved about it like the fact that it’s a hybrid of the Dani Bra and Trail Tank, making it the perfect base layer compression tank. Or that it’s reversible and can be worn with a modest high neck or a sultry cross-over v-neck (that’s also great for chest-feeding 😉). Not to mention that it has the support of the Dani Bra meaning you can go braless and still maintain the support and bust separation that you love!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Dani Tank was met with a lot of love but we did hear a coooouple of requests to make it all that much more perfect. And you know we’re always listening so we did exactly what you asked for! First up, the fit. The Dani Bra has always been the most compressive of our bra styles and with the added fabric to make it into a tanktop, it added even more compression. And so to make it more consistent and true to FL sizing, the Dani Tank has been sized up half a size! This still maintains the hug-like compression while the fit is now pretty dang close to the Dani Bra. Next up, the armhole has been lowered half an inch for the folks who found it too high, but not so low that you lose b🍈🍈b coverage. A subtle change that goes a long way!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So... what do you think of the new and improved Dani Tank 2.0??
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

There’s a reason that this warm-weather staple style is back!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Introduced in 2019, the Rai Crop has been made in three different fabrics (tencel, linen and bamboo) but what’s remained consistent is the fact that it’s the *perfect* chafe-free alternative to shorts. The dramatic ultra-wide leg, breezy side slit, and crop length are the perfect trifecta for a flowy fit. Not to mention the soft stretchy high waistband for ultimate comfort. We introduced the Rai Crop last year in Bamboo and honestly, I wish we’d done it sooner!! The flowy design and cooling buttery soft feel of bamboo are a match made in heaven 😇
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
P.S. After listening to your feedback, we’ve increased the circumference of the Rai Crop waistband by 3/4th of an inch to match the Loretta Pant for a more consistent fit!

Introducing... the first-ever shortline bamboo bra in Free Label history! Meet, the ✨ ELLIE BRA ✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When I said this collection is all about you, I meant it! Early last year, we put a call out on our FB Group to design the next FL bra. Over and over again, we received requests for a shortline bamboo bra. With this in mind, we were playing around with a mix of the Carrie and Becky with a square back when we saw a photo of a Becky Bra that had been altered to have a ruched front that folks loved. And so, the Ellie Bra was born! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Design: 
▫️ Shortline with a 1” elastic band under the bust for support that works for a variety of body shapes
▫️ A ruched front that is not only cute but functional for light bust separation!
▫️ A SQUARE back!! No worries about it peeking out on tops with lower backs. While this bra wasn’t designed to be reversible, all our fit-testers have enjoyed wearing the squareneck in front as long as you don’t mind the ruching on your back. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The Fit: 
▫️ Medium compression similar to the Becky Bra
▫️ Medium support 
▫️ Higher bust coverage 
▫️ Deep cups to accommodate fuller busts
When it comes to choosing your size, I recommend going with your usual FL bra size (no need to size up like some do for the Dani and Carrie! And if you have any questions, feel free to send me a DM :)
